node.text:
@LindbladExp was founded with wanderlust in its DNA. It was certainly present in Lars-Eric Lindblad. In 1966, he successfully led a group of 56 intrepid guests to Antarctica, where only explorers and scientists had ever gone. In 1967 he did it again in Galápagos; effectively inventing expedition travel. Since then, his son Sven Lindblad, has created an unmatched expedition style, taking curious people to the world’s wild, remote places for up-close encounters with beauty, wildness and the seldom-seen, accompanied by expert naturalists…

You’ll see curious minke whales that spent over an hour with the @LindbladExp ship in the first image. Image 2 captures a penguin ‘flying’ through the ocean beneath the ship on another expedition.

Follow @LindbladExp for more wild moments and tag #whereiexplore to share your exploration photos with us.
#LindbladPartner

Photos by: @colbyoutdoors & @footloosefotography
